{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"1c60dc8d-a960-5408-bb52-a60552af342d","excerpt":"Inspiration I have been considering building a standing desk on the cheap.  I read an article where you can get all the parts from Ikea like…","html":"<!-- TODO: Add cover image -->\n<h2 id=\"inspiration\"><a href=\"#inspiration\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Inspiration</h2>\n<p>I have been considering building a standing desk on the cheap. <a href=\"http://iamnotaprogrammer.com/Ikea-Standing-desk-for-22-dollars.html\">I read an article where you can get all the parts from Ikea like for $20 bucks</a> and just make your own. The <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/VARIDESK-Height-Adjustable-Standing-Desk-Pro/dp/B00BBFXBF4\">official Veridesk ones</a> are like a grand and even the one that you put on top of your existing desk runs $300. So yeah, not in my budget at all. Probably need a stool kinda thing in case I get tired standing as well, the veridesk one is insane.</p>\n<h2 id=\"standing-desk-build\"><a href=\"#standing-desk-build\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Standing Desk Build</h2>\n<!-- TODO: Add image -->\n<p>I’ve been wanting a standing desk for some time but was always put off since it was so expensive. I have a regular siting desk for many years but since we got Veridesk at work I’ve enjoyed the health benefits and been wanting one for my home office as well.</p>\n<p>So I looked around and found that there was an Ikea hack where you could build your own for ~$20. I was so happy that I wanted to see if I could pull it off. If it didn’t work out it was just $20 bucks and little bit of my time so no biggie.</p>\n<p>Another problem I faced was that the pieces were from Ikea but the closest one is in Austin which is ~ 2hrs drive. <em>I didn’t feel like spending 4 hours in the car to I could save a few bucks</em>.</p>\n<p>So while we were at Walmart looking around, I took a look around to see if I could find similar materials to make the standing desk.</p>\n<h3 id=\"materials\"><a href=\"#materials\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Materials</h3>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/e87b9/end-table.webp 148w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/404d7/end-table.webp 295w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/6c5da/end-table.webp 590w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/8fbeb/end-table.webp 885w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/ef0b4/end-table.webp 1180w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/e88a2/end-table.webp 1770w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/73636/end-table.webp 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/fc706/end-table.jpg 148w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/754cc/end-table.jpg 295w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/8e0ad/end-table.jpg 590w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/66519/end-table.jpg 885w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/c57d2/end-table.jpg 1180w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/58788/end-table.jpg 1770w,\n/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/78f99/end-table.jpg 4032w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/513aa5eeb93592b210dbdf65728438e0/8e0ad/end-table.jpg\"\n          alt=\"end table from Walmart\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> <a href=\"https://www.walmart.com/ip/Mainstays-Parsons-End-Table-Multiple-Colors/47827019\">end table(monitor stand), $12</a></li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> shelf(keyboard and mouse), $6</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\"><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> brackets(to put them together), $5</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I found a end table in Walmart’s furniture isle. I had a harder time finding the shelf but eventually found it in the tools/hardware area in the closet organizer area. Brackets were also located right next to the shelf since it was the same brand.</p>\n<h2 id=\"bonus\"><a href=\"#bonus\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Bonus</h2>\n<p>You will eventually get tired of standing so there are some bonus items you can get that will make your standing desk more standing friendly.</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\">\n<p><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> <a href=\"https://www.samsclub.com/sams/comfort-mat-20-x-39-black/prod20640234.ip\">anti-fatigue mat</a>, $20</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I found the anti-fatigue mat at Sams in the office furniture area. It is of good quality and really does help your feet stay happy at your standing desk.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"task-list-item\">\n<p><input type=\"checkbox\" disabled> stool, $22</p>\n<ul>\n<li>So you can’t stand forever and too much of a good thing is never good so I also invested in a stool so when I do get tired I can sit and still be high enough to take advantage of the standing desk.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/e87b9/standing-desk.webp 148w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/404d7/standing-desk.webp 295w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/6c5da/standing-desk.webp 590w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/8fbeb/standing-desk.webp 885w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/ef0b4/standing-desk.webp 1180w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/e88a2/standing-desk.webp 1770w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/1e8ee/standing-desk.webp 2626w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/fc706/standing-desk.jpg 148w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/754cc/standing-desk.jpg 295w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/8e0ad/standing-desk.jpg 590w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/66519/standing-desk.jpg 885w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/c57d2/standing-desk.jpg 1180w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/58788/standing-desk.jpg 1770w,\n/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/9bdef/standing-desk.jpg 2626w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/2fcca5e16f063f81ae19cf56074c5939/8e0ad/standing-desk.jpg\"\n          alt=\"happy dev\"\n          title=\"\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </span></p>\n<p>So far I am very happy with the results, glad I didn’t have to spend a fortune, and also leaned into my hacker tendencies. We’ll see if it holds up but if it doesn’t, I can always build another one #onthecheap.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Poorman's Standing Desk","date":"December 17, 2018","slug":"poormans-standing-desk","language":"en","tags":["budget","onthecheap","hacks","diy"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/post-image-a3d5827d2e10e632e38306783a57ada3.jpg"},"imageTw":{"publicURL":"/static/post-image-a3d5827d2e10e632e38306783a57ada3.jpg"},"imageFb":{"publicURL":"/static/post-image-a3d5827d2e10e632e38306783a57ada3.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"poormans-standing-desk","previous":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Top 3 Gartner Application Conference Takeaways","slug":"top3-gartner-takeaways","type":null,"tags":["vision","trends","conference"]}},"next":null}}